    "http://schema.org/url": [
      {
        "@id": "https://ww1.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=7332"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "The Sound of Tarantino"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p><b>Tarantino's film music brought to life on stage!</b></p>\n\n<p>Immerse yourself in the musical world of Quentin Tarantino's films with The Sound of Tarantino, a captivating show presented by the band Black Mamba! In an electrifying and festive atmosphere, 10 seasoned artists will perform iconic tracks from cult classics like Pulp Fiction, Django Unchained, Kill Bill, Inglourious Basterds, Once Upon a Time... in Hollywood, and many more!<br>\nWhile Tarantino is distinguished by his visual style and dark humor, his eclectic soundtracks also play a crucial role in the atmosphere of his films. By combining surf rock, soul, disco, and psychedelic rock, he creates unique sonic universes. His musical choices have even helped revive forgotten songs and launch the careers of now-renowned artists. So, you don't need to be familiar with Tarantino's films to enjoy The Sound of Tarantino; The audience will be delighted to rediscover hits from the 50s to the 70s, and will make some wonderful musical discoveries throughout the show.</p>\n\n<p><b>A Celebration of Tarantino's Universe</b><br>\nThe show's staging will draw inspiration from iconic moments in Tarantino's films. Costumes, choreography, and set design will transport the audience into the director's world.<br>\nVJ Colin Bruneau-Sauvé (VJ Vega) will project film clips and visual animations, adding an immersive dimension to the event. The Sound of Tarantino will appeal to both film buffs and music lovers.</p>\n\n<p>'The Sound of Tarantino' is a groovy show where music takes center stage, plunging you into the unbridled world of cult director Quentin Tarantino. Come discover ten of the best local musicians and singers, accompanied by VJ Vega's visual animation.</p>\n\n \n\n<p><b>Black Mamba - Ten musicians united on stage</b></p>\n\n<p>\n<b>Vicky Martel</b> (performer - <i>Venus 3</i>)<br>\n<b>Christine Dubois</b> (performer - <i>Montreal Rhapsody Orchestra</i>)<br>\n<b>François Bruneau</b> (  guitar, concept and musical direction  - <i>Mange l'Ours Mange, The Box, The Surftronics</i>)<br>\n<b>Maxime Lalanne</b> (drums - <i>Marie-Mai, Ludovick Bourgeois</i>)<br>\n<b>Sébastien Daigle</b> (bass, multi-instruments ans voice - <i>La Chicane, Véronique DiCaire</i>)<br>\n<b>Luc Lemire</b> (saxophone - <i>Éric Lapointe</i>)<br>\n<b>Charles Imbeau</b> (trumpet - <i>Robert Charlebois</i>)<br>\n<b>Dominic Léveillé</b> (trumpet - <i>Pink Martini, M</i>)<br>\n<b>Daniel Volj</b> (guitar et voice - <i>Marie Carmen, The Box</i>)<br>\n<b>Guillaume Jodoin</b> (keyboards - <i>The Box</i>)\n</p>\n\n<p><b>DINNER IS AT THE HEART OF THE SHOW EXPERIENCE!</b><br>\n\nDiscover the menu by <a href='https://esd2026.tor1.digitaloceanspaces.com/uploads/menu-souper-spectacle-studio-cabaret.pdf' target='_blank'>clicking here</a>.<br>\n\nDoors open at 5:30 p.m., and dinner is served from 6:00 p.m. To fully enjoy your meal, we recommend arriving before 6:30 p.m.</p>\n\n<iframe width='560' height='315' src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/hyQ5RuQtx1Y?si=j20kfrwZKgY-f69H' title='YouTube video player' frameborder='0' allow='accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share' referrerpolicy='strict-origin-when-cross-origin' allowfullscreen></iframe>\n\n<style>\n@media screen and (max-width:728px) {\niframe{width:100%!important;}\n}\n</style>"
      }
    ],
